    "Body": " A software development company located in New York City is actively seeking a dedicated and experienced accounting professional for a promising opportunity as their new Regional Controller. In this role, the Regional Controller will be responsible for supervising and organizing the planning for their regional finance team. Apply today! The Regional Controller Will Responsibilities Regularly assess and review goal achievement progress with the team Ensure that the team rigorously organizes and files all documentation per the communicated internal procedure in place Produce monthly group reporting Lead interviews of prospective new hires for the regional finance team Coordinate group closing schedule with external accountants Optimize the tasks of the team and coordinate its schedule according to the group reporting schedule Coordinate the finance tasks with external accountant Promote training and skill development of the team to help them reach competency and expectation levels in the performance of their duties Manage month-end close process Implement and maintain budgets, forecasts and performance reporting in close relation with the Group FP&A Director from the head-office in Luxemburg and his team; Review internal and external accounting reports, financial statements, aging, and cash flow reporting Qualifications 12-15 years of total experience 4-5 years of experience in a Big 4 Firm CPA Experience in Financial Planning and Analysis in a software implementation and support or a professional services environment Significant exposure to US taxes, as well as transfer-pricing and withholding-tax issues Experience with ERP payroll systems Proficiency with Excel (pivot tables), importing/exporting data, Outlook, and MS office Fluency in Spanish Audit and international business administration background Comfortable with US GAAP Desired Skills Fluent in French IFRS knowledge Experience in a small firm Experience with South American entities ", 
